Common causes of anemia include the following: 1  Anemia from active bleeding: Loss of blood through heavy menstrual bleeding or wounds can cause anemia. 2  Iron deficiency anemia: The bone marrow needs iron to make red blood cells. 3  Anemia of chronic disease: Any long-term medical condition can lead to anemia.
